{"word": "rapacious", "meanings": [{"pos": "s", "definition": "living by preying on other animals especially by catching living prey", "synonyms": ["predatory", "raptorial", "ravening", "vulturine", "vulturous"], "examples": ["a predatory bird", "the rapacious wolf", "raptorial birds", "ravening wolves", "a vulturine taste for offal"]}, {"pos": "s", "definition": "excessively greedy and grasping", "synonyms": ["ravening", "voracious"], "examples": ["a rapacious divorcee on the prowl", "ravening creditors", "paying taxes to voracious governments"]}, {"pos": "s", "definition": "devouring or craving food in great quantities", "synonyms": ["edacious", "esurient", "ravening", "ravenous", "voracious", "wolfish"], "examples": ["edacious vultures", "a rapacious appetite", "ravenous as wolves", "voracious sharks"]}]}